---
import PageLayout from "@layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import Container from "@components/Container.astro";
import { ABOUT } from "@consts"; // Asegúrate de definir ABOUT en consts.ts o usa texto directo
---

<PageLayout title="Sobre mí" description="Un poco más sobre quién soy">
  <Container>
    <h4 class="animate text-xl font-semibold text-black dark:text-white mb-6">
      About me
    </h4>
    <div class="space-y-16">
      <!-- Experience -->
      <section>
        <h5 class="animate font-semibold text-black dark:text-white">
          Experience
        </h5>
        <article class="space-y-6">
          <div class="animate">
            <div class="text-sm opacity-75 italic">
              January 2025 – Present
            </div>
            <div class="font-semibold text-black dark:text-white">
              DevOps Engineer — Kumori Systems
            </div>
          
            <article class="mt-2 space-y-3">
              <p>
                Spearheading the modernization of cloud infrastructure by architecting and implementing robust Infrastructure as Code (IaC) solutions using Terraform.
              </p>
              <p>
                Designing modular and reusable Terraform blueprints to automate the provisioning of complex cloud environments, significantly reducing deployment times and eliminating manual configuration drift.
              </p>
              <p>
                Managing the lifecycle and maintenance of multiple Kubernetes clusters, ensuring high availability and orchestrating critical operations such as cluster-wide certificate renewals.
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>

          <div class="animate">
            <div class="text-sm opacity-75 italic">
              December 2023 – December 2024
            </div>
            <div class="font-semibold text-black dark:text-white">
              DevOps Engineer — Instituto de Instrumentación para Imagen Molecular (i3m)
            </div>
          
            <article class="mt-2 space-y-3">
              <p>
                Worked within the Grid and High Performance Computing group, contributing to a European research project.
              </p>
              <p>
                Designed and deployed an end-to-end cloud computing infrastructure on-premises using Kubernetes, managing the platform lifecycle and maintenance.
              </p>
              <p>
                Managed infrastructure microservices using native Kubernetes resources, Helm and Custom Resource Definitions (CRDs), and deployed services such as Jenkins, Keycloak, MinIO, Prometheus, Grafana and MongoDB/MySQL operators.
              </p>
              <p>
                Developed CI/CD pipelines in Jenkins to ensure reproducibility of code hosted on GitHub, and implemented event-driven solutions using Azure Functions to improve scalability.
              </p>
              <p>
                Applied RBAC security policies and integrated Keycloak for user management and access control across the platform.
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>

          <div class="animate">
            <div class="text-sm opacity-75 italic">
              December 2022 – July 2023
            </div>
            <div class="font-semibold text-black dark:text-white">
              DevOps Engineer — Instituto de Automática e Informática Industrial (ai2)
            </div>
          
            <article class="mt-2 space-y-3">
              <p>
                Worked on DevOps and Systems Administration tasks, focusing on containerization, deployment and monitoring of distributed systems.
              </p>
              <p>
                Deployed and managed microservices on Kubernetes using Deployments, Services and Ingress, including robotics simulations and web hosting environments.
              </p>
              <p>
                Set up and configured a Jenkins instance, and developed CI/CD pipelines to automate image building and deployment based on Git commits.
              </p>
              <p>
                Implemented monitoring solutions using Prometheus and Grafana, building dashboards to visualize CPU, memory and GPU usage across cluster nodes.
              </p>
              <p>
                Developed my Master's thesis focused on designing a unified authentication and authorization system for Kubernetes clusters in research environments.
              </p>
              <p>
                Built a Single Sign-On (SSO) solution integrating university credentials, enabling authentication at both microservices and Kubernetes CLI levels using Keycloak and OAuth2 Proxy, and managing access through RBAC policies.
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </article>
      </section>
      <!-- Education -->
      <section>
        <h5 class="animate font-semibold text-black dark:text-white">
          Education
        </h5>
      
        <article class="space-y-6 mt-4">
      
          <div class="animate">
            <div class="text-sm opacity-75 italic">
              2022 – 2023
            </div>
            <div class="font-semibold text-black dark:text-white">
              Master’s Degree in Cloud Computing and High Performance Computing — Universitat Politècnica de València
            </div>
      
            <article class="mt-2 space-y-3">
              <p>
                Completed a Master's program focused on cloud computing and high-performance systems, working on multiple academic projects involving modern cloud-native technologies.
              </p>
              <p>
                Gained hands-on experience with core cloud technologies such as Docker, Kubernetes and Ansible, as well as public cloud platforms including AWS and Azure.
              </p>
              <p>
                Worked with parallel programming models such as MPI and OpenMP, and GPU acceleration technologies including CUDA and OpenCL.
              </p>
              <p>
                Studied Big Data processing techniques and tools, including MapReduce with Apache Hadoop and distributed data processing with Apache Spark.
              </p>
              <p>
                Technologies: Docker, Kubernetes, Ansible, MPI, OpenMP, Shell, CUDA, OpenCL, Apache Hadoop, Apache Spark, Kafka, ZeroMQ
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>
      
          <div class="animate">
            <div class="text-sm opacity-75 italic">
              2018 – 2022
            </div>
            <div class="font-semibold text-black dark:text-white">
              Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Engineering — Universitat Politècnica de València
            </div>
      
            <article class="mt-2 space-y-3">
              <p>
                Completed a Bachelor's degree in Computer Engineering, building a solid foundation in software development, systems and computer science fundamentals.
              </p>
              <p>
                Technologies: Java, C#, C++, HTML, CSS, JavaScript
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>
      
        </article>
      </section>
      <!-- Certifications -->
      <section>
        <h5 class="animate font-semibold text-black dark:text-white">
          Certifications
        </h5>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 animate">
          <li>Certified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA)</li>
          <li>Terraform Associate 004</li>
          <li>C1 Advanced Cambridge</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
  </Container>
</PageLayout>